natural problem: A line goes through point $A(9, 1)$, point $B(19, k)$ and point $C(7, 0)$. What is the value of $k$?
natural solution: The slope of the line is $\frac{1-0}{9-7}=\frac12$, so $\frac{k-1}{19-9}=\frac12$, or $k-1=\frac{10}{2}$ and $k=\boxed{6}$.
